'''Supreme Martial Commander of the Separatist Droid Armies''',<ref name="LS Grievous">{{ForceCollection|General Grievous [Last Stand]|star=5}}</ref> also referred to as '''Supreme Commander of the Droid Army''',<ref name="Character Encyclopedia" /> or '''Supreme Commander of the Separatist droid army''',<ref name="Insider2022">{{InsiderCite|Special Edition 2022|The Grievous Growl}}</ref> was the title held by [[General]] [[Grievous]] during the [[Clone Wars]]. In this capacity,<ref name="Character Encyclopedia" /> he served as the [[Commander-in-Chief|leader]] of the entire [[Confederacy military]]<ref name="Helmet Collection 61" /> throughout the war until his [[Battle of Utapau|demise]] on [[Utapau]].<ref name="Character Encyclopedia" />

{{Military-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|General Grievous&hellip; Supreme Commander of the Droid Armies. You're shorter than I expected.|Anakin Skywalker, in the ''Revenge of the Sith'' screenplay|<ref name="Illustrated Screenplay">[[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith Illustrated Screenplay|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith Illustrated Screenplay'']]</ref>}}
[[File:ScuttlingtoSafety-GeneralGrievous-SWU.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Propaganda-style art of Grievous in his capacity as Supreme Commander for ''[[Star Wars: Unlimited]]'']]
The Supreme Martial Commander of the Separatist Droid Armies position first appeared through the character of Grievous in the [[2005]] film [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']].<ref name="Episode III">{{Film|III}}</ref> It received its full identification through Grievous's five star Last Stand card in ''[[Star Wars: Force Collection]]''<ref name="LS Grievous" /> but has also received numerous alternate names throughout [[canon]].<ref name="Character Encyclopedia" /> The [[2016]] reference book ''[[Star Wars Character Encyclopedia: Updated and Expanded]]''<ref name="Character Encyclopedia" /> and its [[2019]] update ''[[Star Wars Character Encyclopedia, New Edition]]'' identified the title as "Supreme Commander of the Droid Army."<ref name="Character Encyclopedia New">''[[Star Wars Character Encyclopedia, New Edition]]''</ref> Meanwhile, however, its [[2021]] update ''[[Star Wars: Character Encyclopedia, Updated and Expanded Edition]]'' identifies it as "Supreme Commander of the droid army," lower case.<ref name="Character Encyclopedia 2021">''[[Star Wars: Character Encyclopedia, Updated and Expanded Edition]]''</ref> The "[[The Grievous Growl]]" article identifies the title as the "Supreme Commander of the Separatist droid army"<ref name="Insider2022" /> while the novel ''[[Inquisitor: Rise of the Red Blade]]'' calls it "Supreme Martial Commander of the Separatist Army."<ref name="RiseofRed">''[[Inquisitor: Rise of the Red Blade]]''</ref>

In the original draft of ''Revenge of the Sith'', written by director [[George Lucas]] and dated [[April 13]], [[2005]], Grievous is introduced in the film's opening crawl as the "commander of the separatist armies." As of the finalized screenplay, however, his introduction in the opening crawl was simplified to just call Grievous the Confederacy's "droid leader." Nonetheless, as "Supreme Commander of the Droid Armies," the title still saw an outright use in the finalized screenplay: [[Jedi General]] [[Anakin Skywalker]] refers to Grievous by his Supreme Commander title during their meeting aboard the ''[[Invisible Hand]]''.<ref name="Illustrated Screenplay" /> However, that mention was not used in the final film.<ref name="Episode III" />

